What is Celestial Navigation (Star Tracker) for Military?
Celestial Navigation (Star Tracker) systems are advanced optical instruments that identify and track stellar patterns to determine precise positioning, orientation, and navigation data. These systems serve as GPS-independent navigation solutions, making them essential for military missions in environments where satellite signals are degraded, denied, or deliberately jammed. Star trackers use high-sensitivity sensors, onboard processing algorithms, and stellar reference databases to deliver accurate attitude determination for missiles, unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs), spacecraft, and next-generation defense platforms.

